      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(privacy): payload PII redaction and AES-256-GCM encryption at rest",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- **PII redaction**: Detects and masks 6 categories (email, phone, SSN, credit card, IPv4, UUID) across tool outputs, user messages, TTS text, and system prompt context files. Zero-false-positive philosophy — prefers missing PII over corrupting valid technical content.\r\n- **System prompt masking**: Optionally strips hostname, OS, shell, and repo path from the Runtime line; can suppress context file injection entirely.\r\n- **Media blocking**: Drops image/audio/video attachments before they reach LLM providers when `privacy.media.blockAttachments` is enabled.\r\n- **Session encryption at rest**: AES-256-GCM with PBKDF2-SHA256 key derivation (210k iterations). Per-line encryption of JSONL session files with independent IVs and auth tags. Atomic file writes to prevent corruption.\r\n- **Plugin SDK subpath**: New `openclaw/plugin-sdk/privacy-runtime` exposes `redactPiiText` for extensions (used by speech-core TTS).\r\n\r\n### Integration points\r\n\r\n| Data path | Guard | Default |\r\n|---|---|---|\r\n| Tool output text | `privacy.pii.toolOutputs` | ON |\r\n| Inbound user messages | `privacy.pii.userMessages` | OFF (opt-in) |\r\n| TTS speech text | `privacy.pii.enabled` | ON |\r\n| System prompt context files | `privacy.pii.systemPrompt` | ON |\r\n| Media attachments | `privacy.media.blockAttachments` | OFF |\r\n| Session files at rest | `privacy.atRest.enabled` | OFF |\r\n\r\n### Configuration\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\nprivacy:\r\n  enabled: true\r\n  pii:\r\n    enabled: true\r\n    systemPrompt: true\r\n    userMessages: false       # opt-in — redacting user input is destructive\r\n    toolOutputs: true\r\n    categories:\r\n      email: {}               # default placeholder [EMAIL]\r\n      phone: { placeholder: \"[PHONE_NUMBER]\" }\r\n      ssn: { redact: false }  # per-category opt-out\r\n      creditCard: {}\r\n      ipv4: {}\r\n      uuid: {}\r\n  media:\r\n    blockAttachments: false\r\n    warnOnBlock: true\r\n  atRest:\r\n    enabled: true\r\n    passphrase: ${OPENCLAW_ENCRYPTION_KEY}\r\n    pbkdf2Iterations: 210000\r\n  systemPrompt:\r\n    maskHostname: true\r\n    maskRepoPath: true\r\n    maskOs: false\r\n    maskShell: false\r\n    suppressContextFiles: false\r\n```\r\n\r\n### New files\r\n\r\n- `src/privacy/types.ts` — `PrivacyConfig` type definition\r\n- `src/privacy/payload-redact.ts` — PII detection and redaction engine\r\n- `src/privacy/session-encrypt.ts` — AES-256-GCM session file encryption\r\n- `src/plugin-sdk/privacy-runtime.ts` — SDK subpath for extensions\r\n- `src/privacy/payload-redact.test.ts` — 20 unit tests\r\n- `src/privacy/session-encrypt.test.ts` — 16 unit tests\r\n- `src/privacy/inbound-redact.test.ts` — 13 integration tests\r\n\r\n### Modified files\r\n\r\n- `src/config/types.openclaw.ts` — added `privacy?: PrivacyConfig` to `OpenClawConfig`\r\n- `src/agents/system-prompt.ts` — runtime line masking + context file redaction via `buildProjectContextSection`\r\n- `src/agents/pi-embedded-subscribe.handlers.tools.ts` — tool output PII redaction\r\n- `src/agents/pi-embedded-subscribe.handlers.types.ts` — added `\"config\"` to `ToolHandlerParams`\r\n- `src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run.ts` — media attachment blocking\r\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.ts` — inbound user message redaction\r\n- `extensions/speech-core/src/tts.ts` — TTS text PII redaction before speech providers\r\n- `package.json` — registered `./plugin-sdk/privacy-runtime` export\r\n- `scripts/lib/plugin-sdk-entrypoints.json` — added `privacy-runtime` entrypoint\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n\r\n- [x] `pnpm test src/privacy/` — 49 privacy tests pass (3 files: payload-redact, session-encrypt, inbound-redact)\r\n- [x] `pnpm test src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts` — 52 system prompt tests pass\r\n- [x] PII redaction verified for all 6 categories with correct placeholders\r\n- [x] Per-category opt-out and custom placeholders verified\r\n- [x] Disabled/no-op behavior verified (privacy off, pii off, config undefined)\r\n- [x] SSN false-positive guard verified (000, 666, 9xx, group 00, serial 0000 all preserved)\r\n- [x] Runtime line masking verified (hostname, OS, shell, repo path — individual and combined)\r\n- [x] Context file redaction and suppression verified\r\n- [x] AES-256-GCM encryption round-trip verified (encrypt → detect → decrypt → integrity match)\r\n- [x] Wrong passphrase correctly rejected with auth error\r\n- [x] Double-encryption prevention verified\r\n- [x] Batch directory encryption verified (3 files recursive)\r\n- [x] Media blocking verified in 4 modes (disabled, off, on+warn, on+silent)\r\n- [x] End-to-end pipeline verified (all 7 stages in sequence)\r\n- [x] Pre-existing Discord type errors confirmed from main, not this branch\r\n\r\nFull manual verification transcript: [comment #4250195673](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/64234#issuecomment-4250195673)",
